Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia, Grupo Aval, Ecopetrol Advance

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-08-30T16:28:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/colombian-stocks-bancolombia-grupo-aval-ecopetrol-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:14 p.m.  New York  time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.9 percent to 13,592.38, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.7 percent to 1,645.56.  Colombian banks rose after the country’s financial sector
assets grew 14 percent from a year ago to 684 trillion pesos in
June, according to a report released yesterday on the website of
Colombia’s securities regulator.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO), Colombia’s biggest bank, rose 1.2
percent to 28,220 pesos.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores (AVAL)  SA, Colombia’s
largest financial holding company, rose 0.4 percent to 1,180
pesos.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s biggest oil company,
rose 0.9 percent to 3,860 pesos. President Juan Manuel Santos
said he plans to boost the number of troops on the roads in
southern Colombia to help protect oil workers, according to a
statement on the presidential website yesterday.  Oil advanced in New York as  home prices  showed signs of
stabilizing in June.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
